Claims CLAIMS  We claim: 1. A system for mounting sliding doors within a wall system, the system comprising: a connection component defining a first accessory channel and a receptacle adjacent a first end thereof; a track secured to the connection component via a cantilever arm extending into the first accessory channel; a roller in communication with the track; a roller bracket connected to the roller at a first end and connected to a sliding door panel at a second end; and a shroud that substantially encases the track, roller, and roller bracket, the shroud having an upper end connectable to the connection component via the receptacle, wherein the shroud is configured to have a suspended ceiling connected to a lower end thereof, and wherein the connection component, track, roller, and roller bracket are disposable above the suspended ceiling. 2. The system of claim 1, wherein the shroud is configured to substantially block light from traveling from above the ceiling to below the ceiling. 3. The system of claim 1, further comprising a track connection bracket, wherein the track connection bracket connects the track to the connection component, the track connection bracket being configured to secure to the track at a first end and secure to the connection component at the other end via a track connection bracket cantilever arm. 4. The system of claim 1, further comprising a door-opening header module. 5. The system of claim 1, further comprising a ceiling support rail. 6. The system of claim 5, wherein the ceiling support rail supports one or more ceiling components. 7. The system of claim 1, further comprising a slit opening through which the door vertically extends. 8. The system of claim 7, wherein the ceiling is flush on opposing sides of the door and in the doorway. 9. A sliding door mounting system, comprising: a first connection component defining a first accessory channel and a second accessory channel; 

 a track secured to the connection component via a first arm extending into the first accessory channel and a second arm extending into the second accessory channel, wherein the track comprises first and second roller channels; first and second rollers in communication with the first and second roller channels, respectively; a roller bracket connected to the first and second rollers at a first end and connected to a door at a second end; and a shroud that substantially encases the track, roller, and roller bracket, the shroud having an upper end connectable to the first connection component. 10. The system of claim 9, wherein the shroud is configured to have a suspended ceiling connected to a lower end thereof, and wherein the first and second connection components, track, rollers, and roller bracket are disposable above the suspended ceiling. 11. The system of claim 10, wherein the mounting system is configured to be disposed within a space above the suspended ceiling that is less than about a foot in vertical height. 12. The system of claim 10, wherein the shroud is configured to block light from traveling from above the suspended ceiling to below the suspended ceiling. 13. The system of claim 9, wherein the shroud is configured to hide the connection components, track, rollers, and roller bracket from view. 14. The system of claim 9, wherein the first and second connection components are secured together at a connection interface via an interface component. 15. The system of claim 12, the first connection component comprising a first extension arm and the second connection component comprising a second extension arm, wherein a third accessory channel is formed between the first and second extension arms when the first and second connection components are secured together at the connection interface via the interface component. 16. The system of claim 9, further comprising a ceiling support rail. 17. The system of claim 16, wherein the ceiling support rail supports one or more ceiling components. 18. A modular connection component configured to be reversibly secured to one or more additional modular connection components at an attachment interface to form a modular structure, the modular connection component comprising: at least one interface element configured to be aligned with a corresponding interface element of a second modular connection component; a first accessory channel disposed adjacent a first end of the connection component; 

 a receptacle disposed adjacent the first end of the connection component; and at least a first portion of a second accessory channel disposed adjacent a second end of the connection component, wherein the second accessory channel is fully defined when the connection component is secured to another connection component at the attachment interface. 19. The modular connection component of claim 18, further comprising a track secured to the connection component, the track comprising first and second roller channels. 20. The modular connection component of claim 19, further comprising a roller bracket secured to the first and second rollers at a first end and secured to a door at a second end, wherein the door slides back and forth as the rollers roll back and forth within the roller channels.
